        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Based on the data retrieved, I can provide a partial answer. The shortcut codes in SRD-46 use a two-digit year prefix where \"05\" maps to **1905**, not 2005 — the database's shortcut convention uses the last two digits of the year, so a 2005 paper would have a shortcut like `05XX` but those returned are from 1905. The SRD-46 database appears to have data up to the mid-1990s for this system, with the most recent citation being **94VBc** (1994).\n\n---",
